  "description": "Roller shade",
  "aiDescription": "product_type: Flat, single-plane textile panel wound around a horizontal top roller mechanism.; structural_geometry: Single planar sheet of flexible material with no pleats, cells, or folds, operating via vertical rolling action into a cylindrical coil at the head.; fabric_appearance: Flexible textile substrate with a woven structure ranging from tight, dense fiber arrangement to open, mesh-like grid, presenting a uniform surface texture.; visible_hardware: Rigid, weighted horizontal bottom rail attached to the fabric edge. Top roller assembly consisting of a cylindrical tube mechanism, with varying degrees of concealment by a rigid cassette or valance structure. No visible lift cords on the fabric face.; edges_and_details: Straight, clean vertical cut lines along side edges. Bottom edge terminated by a rigid horizontal bar that maintains fabric tension and flatness.; proportions: Extremely slim vertical profile when extended into a flat plane. Retracts into a compact cylindrical stack at the top headrail position.; mounting_topology: Top-mounted installation located at the head of the window opening, positioned either recessed within the frame or on the surface above the frame.",
